texts: I can hear Natsuka diligently weeding the grass.
This May has been consistently sunny. It reminds me of summer in the highlands.
The sunlight is warm and gentle on my skin. I can feel a refreshing breeze on my lips as I listen to the rustling of the grass.
The sweet scent of flowers tickles my nostrils.
The cemetery is bright and filled with greenery, and the lawn around a brand-new gravestone is dotted with yellow flowers.
The name of these flowers is %i1Hemerocallis%id.
The name of these flowers is Hemerocallis.
The name of these flowers is Hemerocallis.
More specifically, the %i1Hemerocallis dumortieri%id, or small daylily. Its flowers bloom for only a single day.
More specifically, the Hemerocallis dumortieri, or small daylily. Its flowers bloom for only a single day.
More specifically, the Hemerocallis dumortieri, or small daylily. Its flowers bloom for only a single day.
Despite its name, the daylily is not actually a lily. Scientifically, it's classified under the %i1Hemerocallidoideae%id subfamily.

Natsuka prepared her sister's new grave herself. When she found out her mother had been carrying her sister's urn with her all this time, she took the appropriate steps to obtain the right to possess the ashes.
I quietly watched over Natsuka as she carried out her decision to part ways with her mother for good.
Inscribed on the gravestone are her sister's name and epitaph. The epitaph is from the book she was clutching in her arms when she passed.
Natsuka said that was the first time she'd ever seen that book.
Due to her sister's blindness, it would have been nearly impossible for her to keep any secrets because she required assistance with even the most basic daily tasks.
Yet, somehow, she had managed to keep something secret from even her family. I was glad to hear that.
MANA UTSUGI.\nToday is a very good day to die.
MANA UTSUGI.Today is a very good day to die.
MANA UTSUGI.Today is a very good day to die.
%i1Mana Utsugi. \nToday is a very good day to die.
Mana Utsugi. Today is a very good day to die.
Mana Utsugi. Today is a very good day to die.
MANA UTSUGI \nToday is a very good day to die.
MANA UTSUGI Today is a very good day to die.
MANA UTSUGI Today is a very good day to die.
\n
That's what's inscribed on the cold, grey stone.
I understand how she felt. Her feelings were valid.
Utsugi Mana, the blind girl. I only know her through Natsuka, but I understand she chose to die out of a desire for freedom. But even in death, she remained bound by her blood.
She's like another me.
I sincerely hope that she has found peace in whatever lies beyond death. For Natsuka's sake, too.
She left Natsuka with a carefully polished, transparent vase... and a blind, peaceful blackness.
After I met Natsuka, I decided I wanted to pay her back for the light she brought me in another form.
I brought the colors of light into Natsuka's blind, black world, adding them to her palette one by one.
Natsuka found the vase within herself... She found her own heart, and she learned to name the feelings in it.
One by one, flowers were added to Natsuka's vase... Flowers of joy, sorrow, and despair. They repainted the landscape of her heart in their colors.
Eventually, Natsuka arrived at her truth.
The black of peace in her heart turned into the white of despair.
Black, white, they're both the same.
When your eyes are peacefully closed, you see nothing. You see just as much when your eyes are blinded by despair.
Still, I prayed she would reach the horizon beyond the white.
She was able to open her eyes amidst the blinding white of despair, and she found herself.
She was able to move on beyond the despair and start walking.
And beyond the white, she found...
Natsuka
"Lilja-san!"
Natsuka
"It's so bright outside today, isn't it? But the breeze feels really nice."
Natsuka
"Mana's flowers have bloomed. They're beautiful."
Natsuka
"I'm really happy to see them. I've always wanted to fill the area around Mana's grave with flowers."
Natsuka
"These flowers only last for a single day, but new flowers replace them every day. She'll be able to enjoy them for a long time."
Lilja
"Yes, surely your sister will be much happier resting here instead of having to deal with her mother's obsession over her even in death."
Natsuka
"You're right. She always wanted to be free, so I'm happy for her, too."
Natsuka
"...All right."
Natsuka
"Let's go home!"
Natsuka
"Hehehe, you look really nice with that parasol. I'm glad I chose it for you."
Natsuka
"Oh, that reminds me. Before Christmas, I was thinking..."
Natsuka
"What would you most want to see? If it's something I could find, then I'd love to give it to you as a present."
Natsuka
"But I didn't have time to look for it back then, so I got you the parasol for Christmas instead..."
Lilja
"I already saw it, so you don't need to worry about that anymore."
Natsuka
"Huh?"
Lilja
"I saw it on Christmas Day."
Natsuka
Natsuka
"Okay..."
Lilja
"But I'm a greedy person, I'll have you know. There's something new I want to see."
Natsuka
"What is it?"
Lilja
"You."
Lilja
"The 'cure' I mentioned before doesn't exist yet. It was a ruse in order to fool Inui. However, it will be developed in the not-so-distant future."
Lilja
"When that happens, I really will be able to %i1see%id you with my own eyes."
"When that happens, I really will be able to see you with my own eyes."
"When that happens, I really will be able to see you with my own eyes."
Natsuka
"That would be incredible!"
Natsuka
"I would love for you to see me, too."
Natsuka
"When I heard your eyes and legs might be cured, it was all I could think about. We talked about it all the time."
Natsuka
"We talked about the joy it would bring, and about the anxiety I felt. About believing, and about staying together... We talked so much."
Natsuka
"I've been thinking about it again lately. I think it'd be okay even if I couldn't make myself useful to you anymore."
Natsuka
"And not because you said it'd be okay if I couldn't help anymore..."
Natsuka
"I remembered how I felt during my first job for you, when I brought you snow in summer..."
Natsuka
"I felt a strong desire to share my feelings with you at that time."
Natsuka
"So, even if I can't be useful to you in the future, I'd still be happy if I could share the things I like with you."
Natsuka
"As long as I feel that way, I'll be fine."
Natsuka
"It turns out I had my answer inside of me all along."
Lilja
"It can be harder to notice something that was there all along, even if it was right in front of you. You need some light to illuminate it and make it visible."
Lilja
"Things only begin to exist when there is light in the world."
Lilja
"Things like the vase you found inside of you."
Lilja
"It was created and polished by your sister, but she didn't create it for you. She made it for herself."
Lilja
"Yet you found it and were able to fill it with flowers of your own."
Lilja
"The flowers in your vase are like paints that give color to the world."
Lilja
"Not just the present world in front of us. They also repaint the past in new colors."
Lilja
"When your present self changes, your past self changes, too. And when the past changes, the present changes along with it."
Lilja
"The future is predicated by the present, which is shaped by the past. It's a never-ending cycle."
Lilja
"Natsuka... When you showed me snow in summer, you said..."
Lilja
"'It was so... beautiful...!'"
Natsuka
"I'm impressed you remember my exact words, Lilja-san."
Lilja
"Once I've seen or heard something, I never forget it."
Lilja
"I've been meaning to ask you for some time why you said it in past tense. Will you tell me, Natsuka?"
Natsuka
"Of course. When I was little, my mom once ripped up a futon my sister had given me."
Natsuka
"At the time, the only thought that went through my head was 'Oh, my futon is torn...'"
Natsuka
"But after you asked me to show you snow in summer..."
Natsuka
"I remembered that moment, and I realized that the feathers floating through the room were beautiful then, too. And I felt relieved to know that I can think of it that way."
Natsuka
"Also..."
Natsuka
"When I remembered how Mom ripped up that futon, I felt a lump in the back of my throat. I think that was probably an urge to cry."
Natsuka
"At the same time, I didn't understand why I should cry over a torn futon."
Natsuka
"When I watched the summer snow with you, Lilja-san, I felt so happy. I realized that at times like those, you should just laugh instead."
Natsuka
"But now, I think about it differently. I know now that it was okay for me to just appreciate the beauty of the torn futon all those years ago."
Natsuka
"And it would've been okay for me to be sad and cry about it, too."
Natsuka
"You were right that when my present self changes, the scenery of my past memories changes as well, over and over again."
Natsuka
Lilja
"It's okay if you want to cry."
Natsuka
"I'm... nngh... crying already... Wahhhhhhh!"
Lilja
Natsuka
"So many things make me cry lately... I've been using a ton of tissues... Wahhhhhh!"
Lilja
"You must have a lot of tears bottled up inside. It's okay to cry until you've let them all out. You'll feel better afterward."
Lilja
"Let me know when you're done crying. Then we can go home."
Natsuka
"Thank youuuuu!"
Natsuka
"*sob* *sob*... Nnnngh!"
Natsuka
"Hahhh... I let out lots of tears again... All right, let's go hom"
Natsuka
"Oh! Right, Lilja-san, can we drop by the shopping district on the way back? I'm sure everyone really wants to meet you."
Lilja
"These are the people who always give you free things, correct?"
Natsuka
"Yeah! I'm sure that when they meet you, they'll want to give you even more freebies than they do me!"
Natsuka
"Flowers, tea, perfume, cake, meat... I'm sure you'll find yourself a pile of wonderful gifts in your lap in no time!"
Natsuka
"Today is the anniversary of the day we met, after all... We should celebrate! Or is that too much? Hehehe!"
Lilja
"Right, it's already been a year since we met."
Natsuka
"Yeah! A year sounds like a long time, but it went by in a flash... Maybe we %i1should%id celebrate?"
"Yeah! A year sounds like a long time, but it went by in a flash... Maybe we should celebrate?"
"Yeah! A year sounds like a long time, but it went by in a flash... Maybe we should celebrate?"
Natsuka
"We didn't get to celebrate your birthday, either, so I've been wondering if we should do something for that, too!"
Lilja
"I didn't think it was necessary."
Natsuka
"Right, and I didn't do anything because you told me not to, but I still want to celebrate!"
Lilja
"You really like parties, don't you?"
Natsuka
"I do! I love celebrating things with you. It's fun, and it makes me really happy."
Lilja
"If we can make it %i1your%id birthday party too, then I'll consider it."
"If we can make it your birthday party too, then I'll consider it."
"If we can make it your birthday party too, then I'll consider it."
Natsuka
"Mine!? Really!? Of course! That'd be amazing! I don't think anyone's ever celebrated my birthday before!"
Lilja
"Think about what you want for your birthday, then."
Natsuka
"A present? Hmm..."
Natsuka
"I know! I wanna get my driver's license. I'd love to be able to drive a camper van. Then, I'd be able to go to way more places than I could on my bicycle!"
Natsuka
"We'll be able to go anywhere!"
Lilja
"Yes, that sounds good. You're my doveyou should spread your wings and fly to the very ends of the land."
Natsuka
"You're coming with me, Lilja-san!!"
Lilja
"What?"
Natsuka
"I want to go out and see all kinds of worlds with you."
Natsuka
"As your eyes and legs, I %i1could%id go and see them in your stead, but..."
"As your eyes and legs, I could go and see them in your stead, but..."
"As your eyes and legs, I could go and see them in your stead, but..."
Natsuka
"I could also just take you with me everywhere!"
Natsuka
"Then we can see the scenery together and share our experiences and feelings."
Lilja
"You sound like you're ready to whisk me away whether I like it or not."
Natsuka
"How would you feel about that?"
Lilja

"Logically speaking, it would be highly inefficient for you to drag me along on your travels, as it would decrease your mobility. However, there may be a certain charm to that type of inefficient travel."
Natsuka
"Yeah!"
Natsuka
"Let's visit all sorts of places together, Lilja-san. I'll take you anywhere you want to goto the bottom of the ocean, above the clouds, and to the end of the rainbow!"
Lilja
"That sounds good. I know I'll be in capable hands with you."
Natsuka
"All right!"
Lilja
(Natsuka's pushing my wheelchair. My skin's directly in touch with the outside world. I can feel the boundary between myself and the world, and I'm remembering what it looked like.)
Lilja
(That's right, Natsuka. I'm sure you'll be able to do it.)
Lilja
(%i1Because%id I've lost my sense of sight, you'll be able to take me to a new world.)
(Because I've lost my sense of sight, you'll be able to take me to a new world.)
(Because I've lost my sense of sight, you'll be able to take me to a new world.)
Lilja
(Just as you've done countless times since I met you, and will continue to do.)
Lilja
(The world as seen through your eyes is much more beautiful than the world I used to see.)
title: To the Future
